<title>USA: International Imaging to buy back shares.</title>
<headline>International Imaging to buy back shares.</headline>
<dateline>AMHERST, N.Y. 1997-04-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>International Imaging Materials Inc said Tuesday its board of directors has authorized it to buy back 500,000 shares, bringing to 634,000 shares its total currently available authorization.</p>
<p>The company reported fourth quarter income of $2.6 million, or $0.29 per share, compared to $3.0 million, or $0.34 per share, for the same period a year ago.</p>
<p>The company also said it expects investments in facilities, sales, marketing and technical resources, which slowed growth and profitibility in fiscal year 1997, to add to its profitability in fiscal 1998.</p>
